The paper discusses techniques for simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) for robots, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses optimization methods and probabilistic formulations, which are topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of off-the-shelf solvers, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of candidate solutions and the computation of optimal solutions, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
